Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
setShrinkFactor(25.10)                                  setShrinkFactor(25.10)

Name
       setShrinkFactor  - Sets the value by which the software shrinks the de-
       sign before extraction

Syntax
       setShrinkFactor

       [-help]

       <shrinkFactor>

       Sets the value by which the software shrinks the design before  extrac-
       tion.  The  shrink  factor is used only for extraction calculations. It
       does not change the actual design.

       Note: You do not need to specify the shrink factor if  the  capacitance
       table  file  in  use  contains  the  shrink factor specification in its
       header.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes type and  default  in-
              formation  for the setShrinkFactor parameter. For a detailed de-
              scription of the command and its parameter, use the man command:

              man setShrinkFactor

       <shrinkFactor>
              Specifies the value by which the software shrinks a design.

              Default: 1.0

Example
       The following command sets the shrink factor to 0.9:

       setShrinkFactor 0.9

       Setting the shrink factor to 0.9 reduces the wire lengths, widths,  and
       spacings in the design by 0.9 times the original values.

